<keyLead pageId="2" pageNumber="524">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,171,399,420]" pageId="2" pageNumber="524">1-</emphasis>
Dorsal surface asetose, body black, lustrous with intensive, green lustre; pronotal disc with rough, transverse rugae (
<figureCitation box="[1352,1425,400,422]" captionStart="FIGS" captionStartId="6.[151,212,1425,1449]" captionTargetBox="[153,1435,185,1397]" captionTargetId="figure-16@6.[151,1436,181,1400]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGS. 10–15. Habitus.10—A. (H.) dispar, female (RSA, Mpumalanga), 7.7 mm; 11—A. (H.) dispar (RSA, Limpopo), male, lateral view, 7.6 mm; 12—A. (H.) keniae Théry, 1941 (Kenya, Kiserian), male, 5.9 mm; 13—A. (H.) occidentalis sp. nov., holotype, male, 7.8 mm; 14—the same, allotype, female, 7.6 mm; 15—A. (H.) pilifrons Kerremans, 1898, (Zambia, Kafue), female, 7.3 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4408011" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4408011/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="524">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
); inner margin of male metatibiae only very weakly emarginate preapically with very weak inner serrations (
<figureCitation box="[1258,1330,429,451]" captionStart="FIGS" captionStartId="9.[151,212,1917,1941]" captionTargetBox="[155,1432,1318,1893]" captionTargetId="figure-459@9.[151,1435,1317,1894]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGS. 23–28. Male metatibiae (not in scale). 23—Anthaxia (Haplathaxia) aethiopica sp. nov., holotype; 24—A. (H.) caerulea sp. nov., holotype; 25—A. (H.) dispar Kerremans, 1898 (RSA, Limpopo); 26—A. (H.) keniae Théry, 1941 (Kenya, Kiserian); 27—A. (H.) occidentalis sp. nov., holotype; 28—A. (H.) pilifrons Kerremans, 1898, holotype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4408017" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4408017/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="524">Fig. 26</figureCitation>
); aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[233,303,458,480]" captionStart="FIGS" captionStartId="8.[151,212,1796,1820]" captionTargetBox="[152,1436,1174,1771]" captionTargetId="figure-414@8.[151,1436,1173,1773]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGS. 16–22. Aedeagi (not in scale). 16—Anthaxia (Haplathaxia) aethiopica sp. nov., holotype; 17—A. (H.) caerulea sp. nov., holotype; 18—A. (H.) dispar Kerremans, 1898 (RSA, Limpopo); 19—A. (H.) keniae Théry, 1941 (Kenya, Kiserian); 20—A. (H.) komareki Obenberger, 1931, holotype; 21—A. (H.) occidentalis sp. nov., holotype; 22—A. (H.) pilifrons Kerremans, 1898, holotype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4408013" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4408013/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="524">Fig. 19</figureCitation>
) almost parallel-sided, elongate; 
<quantity box="[622,740,458,480]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.2" metricValueMax="6.9" metricValueMin="5.5" pageId="2" pageNumber="524" unit="mm" value="6.2" valueMax="6.9" valueMin="5.5">5.5–6.9 mm</quantity>
; 
<collectingCountry box="[750,815,459,480]" name="Kenya" pageId="2" pageNumber="524">Kenya</collectingCountry>
