<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,399,1302]" pageId="2" pageNumber="524">
<keyLead pageId="2" pageNumber="524">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,163,488,509]" pageId="2" pageNumber="524">–</emphasis>
Entire dorsal surface matt with rather long, sometimes almost lanuginose, brown-red or rusty pubescence (
<figureCitation box="[1235,1324,487,510]" captionStart="FIGS" captionStartId="3.[151,212,1858,1882]" captionTargetBox="[251,1343,182,1829]" captionTargetId="figure-24@3.[230,1358,181,1834]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGS. 1–9. Historical types. 1—Anthaxia dispar Kerremans, 1898, holotype, female 7.1 mm; 2—A. hyperlasia Obenberger, 1928, holotype, female, 8.9 mm; 3—A. komareki Obenberger, 1931, holotype, male, 4.8 mm; 4—A. lasioptera Obenberger, 1915, holotype, female, 7.3 mm; 5—A. pilifrons Kerremans, 1898, holotype, male, 7.5 mm; 6—A. vulpes Théry, 1930, holotype, female, 7.2 mm, © MNHN; 7—Anthaxia (Haplathaxia) aethiopica sp. nov., holotype, male, 5.7 mm; 8—A. (H.) caerulea sp. nov., holotype, male, 8.6 mm; 9—A. (H.) dispar Kerremans, 1898, (RSA, Limpopo), male, 7.6 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4408009" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4408009/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="524">Figs. 2, 5</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1334,1361,488,510]" captionStart="FIGS" captionStartId="6.[151,212,1425,1449]" captionTargetBox="[153,1435,185,1397]" captionTargetId="figure-16@6.[151,1436,181,1400]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGS. 10–15. Habitus.10—A. (H.) dispar, female (RSA, Mpumalanga), 7.7 mm; 11—A. (H.) dispar (RSA, Limpopo), male, lateral view, 7.6 mm; 12—A. (H.) keniae Théry, 1941 (Kenya, Kiserian), male, 5.9 mm; 13—A. (H.) occidentalis sp. nov., holotype, male, 7.8 mm; 14—the same, allotype, female, 7.6 mm; 15—A. (H.) pilifrons Kerremans, 1898, (Zambia, Kafue), female, 7.3 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4408011" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4408011/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="524">10</figureCitation>
); sculpture of pronotal disc consisting of fine, simple punctures or fine, polygonal cells with large central grains............... 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1424,1436,517,538]" pageId="2" pageNumber="524">2</emphasis>
</keyLead>
