<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,163,634,655]" pageId="2" pageNumber="524">3</emphasis>
- Smaller species, distal antennomeres of male (4–10) much wider than long; vertex as wide as width of eye; pronotal sculpture homogeneous, lateroposterior depressions missing (
<figureCitation box="[731,791,664,686]" captionStart="FIGS" captionStartId="3.[151,212,1858,1882]" captionTargetBox="[251,1343,182,1829]" captionTargetId="figure-24@3.[230,1358,181,1834]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGS. 1–9. Historical types. 1—Anthaxia dispar Kerremans, 1898, holotype, female 7.1 mm; 2—A. hyperlasia Obenberger, 1928, holotype, female, 8.9 mm; 3—A. komareki Obenberger, 1931, holotype, male, 4.8 mm; 4—A. lasioptera Obenberger, 1915, holotype, female, 7.3 mm; 5—A. pilifrons Kerremans, 1898, holotype, male, 7.5 mm; 6—A. vulpes Théry, 1930, holotype, female, 7.2 mm, © MNHN; 7—Anthaxia (Haplathaxia) aethiopica sp. nov., holotype, male, 5.7 mm; 8—A. (H.) caerulea sp. nov., holotype, male, 8.6 mm; 9—A. (H.) dispar Kerremans, 1898, (RSA, Limpopo), male, 7.6 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4408009" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4408009/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="524">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
); aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[915,987,664,686]" captionStart="FIGS" captionStartId="8.[151,212,1796,1820]" captionTargetBox="[152,1436,1174,1771]" captionTargetId="figure-414@8.[151,1436,1173,1773]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGS. 16–22. Aedeagi (not in scale). 16—Anthaxia (Haplathaxia) aethiopica sp. nov., holotype; 17—A. (H.) caerulea sp. nov., holotype; 18—A. (H.) dispar Kerremans, 1898 (RSA, Limpopo); 19—A. (H.) keniae Théry, 1941 (Kenya, Kiserian); 20—A. (H.) komareki Obenberger, 1931, holotype; 21—A. (H.) occidentalis sp. nov., holotype; 22—A. (H.) pilifrons Kerremans, 1898, holotype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4408013" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4408013/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="524">Fig. 20</figureCitation>
) short, almost spindle-shaped, weakly sclerotised; 
<quantity box="[284,360,693,714]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.8" pageId="2" pageNumber="524" unit="mm" value="4.8">4.8 mm</quantity>
; 
<collectingCountry box="[370,473,693,715]" name="Zimbabwe" pageId="2" pageNumber="524">Zimbabwe</collectingCountry>
...................................................... 
